      • instantiate

        public static java.lang.Object instantiate​(java.lang.Class<?> className)
        Takes a given class as a class object and returns a new instance of that class. Only works for classes with no argument constructors.
        Parameters:
        className - The class to be instantiated as a class object.
        Returns:
        A new instance of the given class. Returned Object needs to be cast to the appropriate type.
